The first Test begins on November 21. The Australian squad includes Steve Smith as captain. England will be led by Ben Stokes.
title: Ashes Test: Massive blow to Australia! Key player ruled out of the 1st Test

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Banks nationwide, except in Jharkhand, will be open today, November 15th, as it is the third Saturday of the month. Customers in Jharkhand will find banks closed due to the Birsa Munda Birth Anniversary. This differs from the usual closure on second and fourth Saturdays, with mobile and net banking remaining accessible.
title: Bank holiday today: Are banks open or closed on November 15? Check details

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google is investing $40 billion in Texas through 2027 to build new cloud and AI infrastructure, including data centers in Armstrong and Haskell Counties. This significant commitment also focuses on strengthening energy resilience with new clean energy resources and expanding the skilled electrical workforce to support the AI era.
title: Google announces $40 bn investment in Texas; CEO Pichai says, ‘proudly called Texas home ’

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US President Trump has eased tariffs on various food items like beef, coffee, and fruits, signaling a policy shift to combat rising consumer costs. This move follows recent election results where economic concerns were prominent. While Trump claims other nations bear tariff costs, Democrats view this as an admission of harm to American shoppers.
title: Grocery bills ease for Americans! Trump cuts tariffs on key food items - what are they?

author: TOI Education
description: The National Commission for Women has called for stricter enforcement of the POSH Act in Higher Educational Institutions, urging stronger redressal systems and comprehensive training. Following the directive, the UGC has asked HEIs to submit updated compliance reports and take part in NCW’s Campus Calling Programme, which includes 800 nationwide sessions on legal literacy, safety, and gender sensitisation.
title: NCW seeks strict POSH compliance; UGC tells colleges to submit reports and step up training

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Bollywood actors Rajkummar Rao and Patralekhaa have welcomed their first child, a baby girl. The happy news arrived on their fourth wedding anniversary, November 15. The couple shared their joy online, calling their daughter God's greatest blessing. Friends and celebrities have sent warm congratulations. This marks a new chapter for the couple, who first met on the sets of 'Citylights'.
title: Rajkummar Rao and Patralekhaa blessed with baby girl on fourth wedding anniversary

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Delhi faces its first Suicide Vehicle-Borne Improvised Explosive Device (SVBIED) attack, a deadly tactic where vehicle parts become lethal projectiles.  These blasts are hard to prevent due to civilian vehicle camouflage and bomber commitment.  Intelligence, public vigilance, and physical barriers are crucial for future prevention.
title: When four wheels become weapons: Delhi’s 1st suicide car bombing exposes new threat — why cops should worry

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: A doctor from Al-Falah University, Dr. Shaheen Shahid, was arrested for her alleged role in a terror plot, attempting to flee to Dubai. Her involvement surfaced after a colleague's arrest and the recovery of an assault rifle from her car. The module, targeting students and doctors, was dismantled through arrests across multiple locations.
title: Delhi car blast case: Terror accused Dr Shaheen applied for passport; planned to flee Dubai

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: An accidental explosion at a Srinagar police station killed four and injured 27, mostly police and forensic personnel, while examining explosives from a 'white-collar' terror module. The blast occurred during sample extraction from 360 kg of materials seized from an arrested doctor's residence, damaging the police station.
title: J&K: CCTV footage captures moment massive blast hit J&K police station; 7 killed

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Oakland police identified Cedric Irving Jr. as the suspect in the fatal shooting of Laney College football coach John Beam. The incident occurred Thursday at the campus fieldhouse, leading to a lockdown. Irving Jr. was arrested Friday morning while armed, following an overnight search. The motive for the shooting remains under investigation.
title: Who is Cedric Irving Jr? Oakland police name suspect as Laney College mourns John Beam
